ol.li:
69. A method, comprising:
determining a time variation in an interference level experienced by a receiver;
generating a first channel estimate of a wireless communication channel as of a first time;
generating a second channel estimate of the wireless communication channel as of a second time;
weighting the first channel estimate and the second channel estimate in accordance with the time variation, thereby generating a first weighted channel estimate and a second weighted channel estimate; and
computing a weighted channel estimate based upon the first weighted channel estimate and the second weighted channel estimate.

73. A computer program product comprising a computer readable medium including codes for causing a computer to:
determine a time variation in an interference level experienced by a receiver;
generate a first channel estimate of a wireless communication channel as of a first time;
generate a second channel estimate of the wireless communication channel as of a second time;
weight the first channel estimate and the second channel estimate in accordance with the time variation, thereby generating a first weighted channel estimate and a second weighted channel estimate; and
compute a weighted channel estimate based upon the first weighted channel estimate and the second weighted channel estimate.
